-- Nigeria to raise $1 bln in treasury bills on June 18
-- By Oludare Mayowa
-- Fri Jun 13, 2014 11:10AM EDT
-- None



LAGOS, June 13 (Reuters) - The central bank said on Friday it would issue short-dated treasury bills on June 18 to raise 168.3 billion naira ($1.03 bln), part of a debt issuance programme it announced this week.

The bank plans to raise 33.26 billion naira in 3-month bills, 65.02 billion naira in 6-month, and 70 billion of one-year notes, using a reverse Dutch auction system.